  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "HR Executive",
  "description": "<p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Handle end-to-end HR operations, including employee onboarding, offboarding, confirmation, and personnel records management</p></li><li><p>Manage recruitment activities such as job posting, resume screening, interview coordination, and offer preparation</p></li><li><p>Liaise with hiring managers to understand manpower requirements and recruitment timelines</p></li><li><p>Administer HR policies, procedures, and ensure compliance with MOM and relevant employment regulations</p></li><li><p>Support foreign manpower matters including work pass applications, renewals, and cancellations (if applicable)</p></li><li><p>Coordinate employee benefits, insurance, and statutory submissions (CPF, SDL, etc.)</p></li><li><p>Handle employee queries and provide day-to-day HR support</p></li><li><p>Support audits, HR reports, and ad-hoc HR projects as assigned<br /></p></li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Diploma or Degree in Human Resource Management or related field</p></li><li><p>Minimum 2–3 years of HR experience, preferably in the construction industry</p></li><li><p>Strong knowledge of HR operations and recruitment processes</p></li><li><p>Familiar with Singapore employment laws and MOM requirements</p></li><li><p>Payroll processing knowledge will be an added advantage</p></li><li><p>Good interpersonal and communication skills</p></li><li><p>Able to work independently and handle confidential information professionally</p></li></ul>",
